race.comment: Wide open with a host of chances. SATISFIED MUGS (3) won first two from a break then could manage only fifth last time here in 3yo class. Boasts a great record course and distance and can bounce back. CORBUSIER (7) returned form a break at Cairns sitting just off the pace and ran right away. Goes well here and drawn for a good run again. Can go on with it. KAI MONDO (9) was beaten less than a length at the Sunny Coast last time. Speedy type with a strong record this trip and will take catching. HENRY'S BLADE (8) is another contestant with strong early pace and has drawn the inside. Goes well fresh and will be in this for a long way. HAND GRENADE (11) will be at her peak and appeals as one of the leading chances.
